owl:Ontology.dc:description: Meta-Share ontology v2. The ontology caters for the description of Language resources (corpora, lexical/conceptual resources, models, grammars, etc. and language processing tools and services) for Language Technology needs. It is also related to the OMTD-SHARE ontology (http://w3id.org/meta-share/omtd-share/) which caters for specific features (LT operation/area, data format, method, annotation type).

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A branch of science (such as biology, medicine, and sometimes anthropology or sociology) that deals with living organisms and life processes —usually used in plural

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: LSID

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: a dictionary usually meant for humans in a form that a computer can process
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Machine Readable Dictionary

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Process mode' and its subclasses used for processes that are performed manually
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: manual

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: a resource consisting of mapping values and/or rules between two resources
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: mapping of resources

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Process mode' and its subclasses used for mixed processes, usually involving an automatic processing followed by human edits
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: mixed

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Linguality type' for resource (parts) which include material in one language
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: monolingual

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: a lexicon with morphological information associated with its entries
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: morphological lexicon

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'EncodingLevel' for the particular linguistic level that relates to the study of word formation (such as inflection, derivation and compounding)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: morphology

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Linguality type' for resource (parts) which include material in three or more languages
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: multilingual

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Multilinguality type' for resource parts or resources that consist of segments including text in two or more languages (e.g., the transcription of a European Parliament session with MPs speaking in their native language)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: multilingual single text

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Funding type' for projects funded by national authorities
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: national funds

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ConditionOfUse' which states that the users of the resource are not allowed to share derivatives of the resource
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: no derivatives

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ConditionOfUse' which states that users are not allowed to redistribute the resource
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: no redistribution

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ConditionOfUse' which states that the language resource cannot be used for commercial purposes, i.e. where there is some direct profit from using it
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: non-commercial use

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for LRTIdentifierScheme referring to the OAI identifier (Open Archives Initiative, http://www.openarchives.org/OAI/2.0/guidelines-oai-identifier.htm)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: OAI

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for LRTIdentifierScheme referring to the identifier assigned by the OpenMinTeD platform (https://services.openminted.eu/home)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: OMTD

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: OMTD-Docker

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Documentation type' for the online help site of a language resource
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: online help URL

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: only META-SHARE members
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:note: should we also add something more generic for restricting a resource to specific group members (as for spatial constraint)? and I don't think the odrl is ok.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: a set of concepts and categories in a subject area or domain that shows their properties and the relations between them [https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/ontology]
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: ontology

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The free and online availability of literature, which allows to read, download, copy, distribute, print, search, or link to the ful text, crawl articles for indexing, pass them as data to software, or use them for any other useful purpose. An availability that is granted without financial, legal, or technical barriers other than those inseparable from gaining access to the internet itself, and those related to giving authors control over the integrity of their work and the right to be properly acknowledged and cited.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: open access

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Funding type' for self-funded projects
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: own funds

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for data distribution medium, used for language resources that are delivered in paper format
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: paper copy

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Multilinguality type' for resource parts or resources that consist of the equivalent text segments in two or more languages (e.g., an original and its translation equivalents)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: parallel

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'EncodingLevel' for the particular linguistic level that relates to the study of speech sounds
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: phonetics

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'EncodingLevel' for the particular linguistic level that relates to the study of speech sounds that constitute the fundamental components of a language
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: phonology

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for software distribution form, used for software objects in the form of plugins (e.g. Chrome browser extension)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: plugin

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for resourceIdentifierSchemeName, referring to the PMCID (PubMed Central Identifier, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pmctopmid/)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: PMCID

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for resourceIdentifierSchemeName, referring to the PMID (PubMed Identifier, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/pmctopmid/)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: PMID

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'EncodingLevel' for the particular linguistic level of analysis that studies the relationship of sentences to the environment in which they occur
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: pragmatics

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Documentation type' used for published documents about a language resource (mainly meant for documents that describe the resource itself rather than its deployment)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: publication

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Documentation type' for a published document describing the language resource and which is recommended by the resource creator(s) to be used for citation purposes when the resource is mentioned in another publication
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: publication for citation

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Version type' used for versions as published in digital or print form
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: published

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The form of the corpus that has not been enriched with annotations
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: raw corpus

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ConditionsOfUse' which states that users are encouraged to deposit any modified versions of the resource they make to the distribution channel through which they have acquired the resource
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: redeposit

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ConditionOfUse' that states that the licensor requires the submission of a research plan in order to grant access to the language resource
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: request plan

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ConditionOfUse' stating that the resource can be used only for research purposes
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: research use

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Access is subject to restrictions or controls regarding users (e.g., limited to researchers or members of a specific group) or use (e.g., for research only, noncommercial use , etc.); subscription or registration may also be required and access may incur financial costs
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: restricted access

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'DocumentationType' used for samples of a language resource
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: samples

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Scholarly communication can be defined as “the system through which research and other scholarly writings are created, evaluated for quality, disseminated to the scholarly community, and preserved for future use. The system includes both formal means of communication, such as publication in peer-reviewed journals, and informal channels, such as electronic listservs.” (Association of College & Research Libraries, “Principles and Strategies for the Reform of Scholarly Communication 1,” 2003)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: scholarly communication

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for personIdentifierSchemeName, referring to the Scopus identifier for authors (https://www.scopus.com)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Scopus ID

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'EncodingLevel' for the particular linguistic level of analysis that relates to the meaning of a word, phrase, etc.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: semantics

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ConditionOfUse' that states that the derivatives of the language resource must be distributed with the same or a compatible licence
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: share alike

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ModalityType' for sign languages represented in a language resource
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: sign language

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: The social sciences are academic disciplines concerned with the study of the social life of human groups and individuals including anthropology, economics, geography, history, political science, psychology, social studies, and sociology. The social sciences consist of the scientific study of the human aspects of the world.[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:Social_sciences
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: Social Sciences

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for software distribution form, used for software that is available from the same location both as source code and executable program
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: source and executable code

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for software distribution form, used for software objects in the form of source code, i.e. as files with the commands ready to be compiled or assembled into an executable computer program
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: source code

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ConditionsOfUse' which is used for resources with spatial restrictions, e.g., in cases where the content is available or can be used only at a single location, center, or site
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: spatial constraint

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ModalityType' for language resources including spoken language words and expressions
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: spoken language

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'Version type' used for versions as submitted for publication
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: submitted

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'EncodingLevel' for the particular linguistic level that relates to the study of the structure of linguistic units (phrases, sentences)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: syntax

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: a flat list of valid values (tags) designed to annotate data; it usually corresponds to a specific annotation type or set of annotation types
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: tagset

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A lexical resource that lists concepts pertaining to a specific domain
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: terminological resource

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'MediaType' for the written or printed form of a language resource (part)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: text

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A reference work that lists words grouped together according to similarity of meaning (containing synonyms and sometimes antonyms) [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thesaurus]
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: thesaurus

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'DocumentationType' used for the training material of a resource (e.g., video tutorials, screencasts, guided tours, etc.)
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: training resource

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ConditionOfUse' which states that the resource can only be used for training purposes
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: training use

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: For resources whose availability is still pending.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: user identified

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: user manual

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: video

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for 'ModalityType' for voice
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: voice

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Value for software distribution form, used for software objects that can be accessed through remote invocation typically using some REST-style APIs or SOAP protocols
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: web service

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A lexical database originally created for English and extended to other languages, which groups words into sets of synonyms called synsets, provides short definitions and usage examples, and records a number of relations among these synonym sets or their members
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: WordNet

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: A written collection of all words derived from a particular source, or sharing some other characteristic [https://www.yourdictionary.com/wordlist]
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: wordlist

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: workflow file

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: written language

For resources that are documented in the catalogue but the contents of which can only be accessed through other distribution channels.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Available Through Other Distributor

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Links to the document used as guidelines for the creation or annotation of a corpus
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: guidelines

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Links a resource to the licence under which it is distributed; values are taken from a list of standard licences
The telephone number of a person or an organization; recommended format: +_international code_city code_number
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: telephone number

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Embargoed access refers to a resource that is metadata only access until released for open access on a certain date. Embargoes can be required by publishers and funders policies, or set by the author (e.g such as in the case of theses and dissertations).
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: embargoed access
In Copyright - Rights-holder(s) Unlocatable or Unidentifiable

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Metadata only access refers to a resource in which access is limited to metadata only. The resource itself is described by the metadata, but neither is directly available through the system or platform nor can be referenced to an open access copy in an external journal or trustworthy archive.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: metadata only access
No Copyright - Other Known Legal Restrictions

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Open access refers to a resource that is immediately and permanently online, and free for all on the Web, without financial and technical barriers.The resource is either stored in the repository or referenced to an external journal or trustworthy archive.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: open access

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Restricted access refers to a resource that is available in a system but with some type of restriction for full open access. This type of access can occur in a number of different situations. Some examples are described below: The user must log-in to the system in order to access the resource The user must send an email to the author or system administrator to access the resource Access to the resource is restricted to a specific community (e.g., limited to a university community)
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: restricted access
